# 1. View full commit history
git log

# 2. View short commit history (compact)
git log --oneline

# 3. View history of a specific file (optional)
git log README.md

# 4. Search for a specific commit by message
git log --grep="Updated README"

# 5. Copy the commit hash (first column in output)
# Example output:
# a1b2c3d Updated README from MITS branch

# 6. Use the commit hash (example)
git show a1b2c3d
